1
00:00:11,533 --> 00:00:13,867
I remember Elsa and Eva.

2
00:00:13,933 --> 00:00:15,133
I wonder how they are.

3
00:00:15,200 --> 00:00:17,233
I enabled you
because I love you.

4
00:00:17,300 --> 00:00:21,167
You never loved me.
You controlled my life!

5
00:00:21,233 --> 00:00:22,267
What's that?

6
00:00:22,333 --> 00:00:25,833
Some use it to make others sick.

7
00:00:25,900 --> 00:00:28,700
Never show up
to me and my daughter

8
00:00:28,767 --> 00:00:30,267
while I'm looking for a buyer.

9
00:00:30,333 --> 00:00:32,600
I'm asking you.
Where are you going?

10
00:00:32,667 --> 00:00:34,067
I'm going to Mommy Emma.

11
00:00:34,167 --> 00:00:36,667
- You have no other choice!
- Ma'am! Ma'am! Ma'am!

12
00:00:38,200 --> 00:00:40,700
I hope we see the woman
in the hotel, Emma.

13
00:00:40,767 --> 00:00:44,133
The taxi driver didn't see the
woman getting inside the hotel.

14
00:00:44,200 --> 00:00:47,933
Thank you so much.
Thank you. Thank you.

15
00:00:48,867 --> 00:00:51,200
- Flor, don't let Mookie out!
- Hit me! Hard!

16
00:00:51,267 --> 00:00:54,133
- Flor, stop her!
- Ma'am! Ma'am!

17
00:00:54,200 --> 00:00:55,167
Mookie!

18
00:01:30,833 --> 00:01:34,333
I'll make sure
you can never escape.

19
00:01:34,400 --> 00:01:37,600
Mommy! Mommy, please.
Let me go! Mommy!

20
00:01:37,667 --> 00:01:39,000
I don't want to!

21
00:01:39,067 --> 00:01:40,533
No! No!

22
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:41,567
No!

23
00:01:43,167 --> 00:01:44,667
Let me go!

24
00:01:44,733 --> 00:01:45,933
I don't want to!

25
00:01:46,500 --> 00:01:49,100
Mommy, please! Let me go!

26
00:01:49,467 --> 00:01:51,533
You can never leave!

27
00:01:51,600 --> 00:01:52,767
Let go!

28
00:01:52,833 --> 00:01:54,033
You're so evil!

29
00:01:54,100 --> 00:01:55,167
You're so bad!

30
00:01:55,233 --> 00:01:56,400
I don't want you
as my mother anymore!

31
00:01:56,467 --> 00:01:59,300
I wish you weren't my mother!

32
00:01:59,367 --> 00:02:01,333
How dare you say that?

33
00:02:01,400 --> 00:02:05,600
I'll make sure
you can never leave this place!

34
00:02:06,700 --> 00:02:09,833
- You're so evil!
- Flor, help me!

35
00:02:09,900 --> 00:02:11,067
I don't want to!

36
00:02:11,133 --> 00:02:14,100
- Let go!
- She doesn't let go, Ma'am!

37
00:02:14,200 --> 00:02:16,400
You're useless!

38
00:02:19,133 --> 00:02:21,067
Mookie! Stay there.

39
00:02:21,133 --> 00:02:23,433
I'll get your wheelchair
so you can escape.

40
00:02:23,500 --> 00:02:24,500
Don't go anywhere.

41
00:02:24,567 --> 00:02:26,000
Wait, I'll be right back.

42
00:02:32,633 --> 00:02:34,500
Mommy, what are you going to do?

43
00:02:34,567 --> 00:02:36,567
Let see if you can resist this!

44
00:02:36,633 --> 00:02:39,100
No! Mommy, no! No!

45
00:03:28,133 --> 00:03:29,100
Mommy?

46
00:03:30,500 --> 00:03:31,667
Mommy?

47
00:03:33,533 --> 00:03:36,333
Mommy! Mommy!

48
00:03:38,467 --> 00:03:39,533
Mommy!

49
00:03:42,933 --> 00:03:44,100
Mommy!

50
00:03:45,600 --> 00:03:46,933
Mommy!

51
00:03:47,967 --> 00:03:49,367
Mommy!

52
00:03:50,600 --> 00:03:52,367
Mommy!

53
00:03:58,933 --> 00:04:00,367
Mommy, please!

54
00:04:00,433 --> 00:04:01,567
Please!

55
00:04:04,067 --> 00:04:05,933
Mommy, please!

56
00:04:26,633 --> 00:04:28,100
I'm going to leave, Mommy.

57
00:04:28,200 --> 00:04:29,600
You have nowhere else to go.

58
00:04:29,667 --> 00:04:31,533
I'm everything you've got.

59
00:04:31,600 --> 00:04:33,967
No. I'll go to Mommy Emma.

60
00:04:34,033 --> 00:04:35,200
She'll take care of me.

61
00:04:35,267 --> 00:04:37,267
She won't do
everything you did to me.

62
00:04:37,333 --> 00:04:40,100
She will never make me sick.

63
00:04:40,167 --> 00:04:44,400
Why are you so stubborn, Mookie?

64
00:04:46,467 --> 00:04:48,767
Aren't we happy?

65
00:04:48,833 --> 00:04:54,900
Why are you trying to find out
things you shouldn't know?

66
00:05:01,167 --> 00:05:05,800
All the people I love leave me.

67
00:05:08,467 --> 00:05:12,300
They all leave me.

68
00:05:12,367 --> 00:05:15,900
I'm so tired of being alone.

69
00:05:18,633 --> 00:05:20,767
Mookie!

70
00:06:17,967 --> 00:06:18,900
Hey.

71
00:06:18,967 --> 00:06:20,667
- Why are you still up?
- Mom.

72
00:06:22,100 --> 00:06:24,233
We can't sleep, Mom.

73
00:06:24,300 --> 00:06:27,200
Aren't you leaving early
tomorrow to see the woman?

74
00:06:27,267 --> 00:06:28,533
You should be sleeping
right now.

75
00:06:28,600 --> 00:06:29,933
Try to get some sleep.

76
00:06:31,633 --> 00:06:32,867
I'll take care of that.

77
00:06:32,933 --> 00:06:35,733
I'll wash those cups
and put them away.

78
00:06:39,233 --> 00:06:40,533
Don't worry.

79
00:06:41,467 --> 00:06:43,800
You'll find Baby Kayla.

80
00:06:46,133 --> 00:06:48,033
Just trust that it'll happen.

81
00:06:51,233 --> 00:06:52,233
I'll do that.

82
00:07:20,900 --> 00:07:21,800
Mommy.

83
00:07:23,600 --> 00:07:25,167
Hi, Mookie.

84
00:07:39,167 --> 00:07:41,100
You missed one.

85
00:07:41,167 --> 00:07:42,633
Mommy...

86
00:07:42,700 --> 00:07:44,833
Mommy, please. Please.

87
00:07:44,900 --> 00:07:45,967
Don't.

88
00:07:48,367 --> 00:07:49,733
Please.

89
00:07:49,800 --> 00:07:51,267
Be quiet.

90
00:07:52,433 --> 00:07:54,833
You might wake them all up.

91
00:08:07,667 --> 00:08:12,533
Mommy, don't you love me?

92
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:16,967
Why will you hurt me, Mommy?

93
00:08:17,033 --> 00:08:23,133
You won't hurt me
if you love me.

94
00:08:23,233 --> 00:08:24,500
Right, Mommy?

95
00:08:26,333 --> 00:08:28,233
Mommy, promise...

96
00:08:28,300 --> 00:08:30,067
I promise, Mommy.

97
00:08:30,133 --> 00:08:32,533
I will never leave you.

98
00:08:32,600 --> 00:08:34,333
Promise.

99
00:08:35,700 --> 00:08:36,800
Really?

100
00:08:44,733 --> 00:08:46,700
No matter what happens...

101
00:08:49,300 --> 00:08:51,667
you won't leave Mommy?

102
00:08:52,700 --> 00:08:53,700
Yes.

103
00:08:54,833 --> 00:08:56,067
Promise, Mommy.

104
00:08:57,300 --> 00:08:59,467
I will never leave you.

105
00:09:19,600 --> 00:09:21,167
I remember.

106
00:09:23,767 --> 00:09:25,633
Your Aunt Jade...

107
00:09:28,533 --> 00:09:31,600
said the same thing to me.

108
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:37,333
Your dad.

109
00:09:42,767 --> 00:09:44,467
They told me...

110
00:09:48,767 --> 00:09:50,833
they would never leave me.

111
00:09:55,667 --> 00:09:57,833
I begged them.

112
00:10:03,167 --> 00:10:05,633
But they still left me.

113
00:10:14,833 --> 00:10:15,667
Mommy.

114
00:10:16,733 --> 00:10:18,967
Mommy, I'm different.

115
00:10:20,333 --> 00:10:24,900
I will never leave you, Mommy.

116
00:10:24,967 --> 00:10:26,933
Promise.

117
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:28,800
Promise, Mommy.

118
00:10:28,867 --> 00:10:31,000
I will never leave you.

119
00:10:32,200 --> 00:10:33,567
Promise.

120
00:10:33,633 --> 00:10:34,733
Liar!

121
00:10:37,600 --> 00:10:40,833
You tried to escape many times.

122
00:10:42,667 --> 00:10:45,300
So I don't trust you anymore!

123
00:10:45,367 --> 00:10:46,467
Mommy, promise!

124
00:10:46,533 --> 00:10:48,467
Promise, Mommy.
I will never leave you.

125
00:10:48,533 --> 00:10:49,733
Promise.

126
00:10:49,800 --> 00:10:51,033
Promise, Mommy.

127
00:10:55,833 --> 00:10:56,833
No, Mommy!

128
00:11:05,367 --> 00:11:07,600
Ouch, Mommy!

129
00:11:08,867 --> 00:11:11,967
Mommy, you're so evil!

130
00:11:17,567 --> 00:11:19,133
Bukoy, we're almost there.

131
00:11:20,067 --> 00:11:21,167
I just got here, too.

132
00:11:22,300 --> 00:11:24,233
Yes, I came from far away.

133
00:11:24,300 --> 00:11:25,467
Where are you now?

134
00:11:26,500 --> 00:11:28,600
Is that so? Okay.
I'll wait for you here.

135
00:11:28,667 --> 00:11:29,733
Hurry up.

136
00:11:29,800 --> 00:11:32,767
The woman's here.
She's getting out of the hotel.

137
00:11:32,833 --> 00:11:34,033
She's leaving.

138
00:11:34,100 --> 00:11:36,100
We're so near, Bukoy.

139
00:11:38,167 --> 00:11:39,300
Are you still far away?

140
00:11:40,367 --> 00:11:41,667
Hurry up, Danilo.

141
00:11:46,233 --> 00:11:47,367
Okay.

142
00:11:51,133 --> 00:11:52,267
Boss, Boss.

143
00:11:52,333 --> 00:11:55,433
I know the woman you assisted
to the van.

144
00:11:55,500 --> 00:11:56,433
- Where is she going?
- She's on the way
to the airport.

145
00:11:57,500 --> 00:11:58,600
- Airport?
- Yes.

146
00:11:58,667 --> 00:12:00,067
Okay, thank you.

147
00:12:02,100 --> 00:12:04,367
Emma, Danilo.
She's on the way to the airport.

148
00:12:04,433 --> 00:12:06,000
Where are you? Hurry!

149
00:12:09,100 --> 00:12:10,333
Hurry! Hurry up!

150
00:12:11,667 --> 00:12:13,433
- Get in! Hurry, get in!
- Get in! Come on!

151
00:13:29,367 --> 00:13:30,700
Mookie! Mookie!

152
00:13:30,767 --> 00:13:34,233
Here's the key.
I took it from your mom's room.

153
00:13:34,300 --> 00:13:36,733
Wait. I'll help you.

154
00:13:36,800 --> 00:13:39,267
Gather all your
remaining strength.

155
00:13:39,333 --> 00:13:41,133
I'll get you out of here. Okay?

156
00:13:41,200 --> 00:13:42,567
- Flor...
- Wait.

157
00:13:56,800 --> 00:14:00,567
It's not just your legs that
will be paralyzed, Mookie.

158
00:14:01,467 --> 00:14:04,333
Your entire body will be
as well.

159
00:14:04,400 --> 00:14:05,733
But don't worry.

160
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:09,367
Mommy's here
to take care of you.

161
00:14:19,767 --> 00:14:21,367
God, please help us.

162
00:14:23,300 --> 00:14:26,233
Where is it?
There are too many keys. My God.

163
00:14:26,300 --> 00:14:27,800
- Wait.
- Faster, Flor.

164
00:14:27,900 --> 00:14:29,467
Yes, yes.

165
00:14:40,333 --> 00:14:41,667
- Where is she, Bukoy?
- There's the woman!

166
00:14:41,733 --> 00:14:42,667
- There she is!
- Where?

167
00:14:42,733 --> 00:14:43,867
- The one in red!
- Who?

168
00:14:43,933 --> 00:14:45,467
- Red?
- Come on! Let's follow her.

169
00:14:45,533 --> 00:14:46,167
Hurry!

170
00:14:48,500 --> 00:14:49,900
Ma'am, excuse me. Hold on.

171
00:14:49,967 --> 00:14:51,200
- Do you have a ticket?
- Sir, Sir.

172
00:14:51,267 --> 00:14:53,767
The kidnapper went inside.
The woman.

173
00:14:53,833 --> 00:14:54,767
I'm sorry, Ma'am.

174
00:14:54,833 --> 00:14:56,900
You can't go inside
without a ticket.

175
00:14:56,967 --> 00:14:58,533
I don't have a ticket,
but I need to catch the woman!

176
00:14:58,600 --> 00:14:59,967
You're not allowed to do that!

177
00:15:00,033 --> 00:15:02,067
- You're not allowed to do that!
- Go ahead and search for her!

178
00:15:02,167 --> 00:15:03,433
I'm sorry, Sir.

179
00:15:03,500 --> 00:15:07,200
Sir, I need to catch the woman!
Sir, I need to catch the woman!

180
00:15:11,133 --> 00:15:13,333
- I'm sorry, Ma'am.
- Wait! Wait a minute.

181
00:15:13,400 --> 00:15:14,900
We need to catch the woman.

182
00:15:14,967 --> 00:15:16,633
A kidnapper is inside!

183
00:15:16,700 --> 00:15:17,733
I'm sorry that is not allowed.

184
00:15:17,800 --> 00:15:18,733
- They might arrest us...
- I'm sorry.
- let's go.
- You really can't get in.

185
00:15:19,800 --> 00:15:21,300
You really can't get in.
I'm sorry.

186
00:15:21,367 --> 00:15:22,633
- Okay, Sir.
- Wait a minute.

187
00:15:22,700 --> 00:15:23,733
I'm begging you.

188
00:15:23,800 --> 00:15:28,200
- Emma, Emma.
- We need to talk to that woman.

189
00:15:28,967 --> 00:15:30,967
Please leave.

190
00:15:33,733 --> 00:15:34,667
Let's go.

191
00:15:39,467 --> 00:15:39,500
Flor, thank you.

192
00:15:41,400 --> 00:15:43,200
There. There!

193
00:15:43,267 --> 00:15:45,200
The other one.

194
00:15:45,267 --> 00:15:46,533
Wait.

195
00:15:48,867 --> 00:15:49,767
There.

196
00:15:53,300 --> 00:15:54,700
Flor.

197
00:15:58,867 --> 00:16:01,267
Why are there so many keys!

198
00:16:02,033 --> 00:16:03,400
This is tough.

199
00:16:06,667 --> 00:16:07,933
You can do it, Flor.

200
00:16:11,200 --> 00:16:12,133
Just one left.

201
00:16:12,200 --> 00:16:13,333
Just one more.

202
00:16:13,400 --> 00:16:15,767
- Thank you, Flor.
- I'm on it.

203
00:16:18,500 --> 00:16:19,900
Traitor!

204
00:16:19,967 --> 00:16:21,200
Ma'am! Ma'am!

205
00:16:21,267 --> 00:16:22,600
You are a traitor!

206
00:16:22,667 --> 00:16:23,567
Ma'am.

207
00:16:26,333 --> 00:16:28,967
Flor!

208
00:16:29,033 --> 00:16:30,667
Get out of here!

209
00:16:30,733 --> 00:16:31,700
Get lost!

210
00:16:50,300 --> 00:16:51,000
Oh.

211
00:16:51,933 --> 00:16:53,333
Drink some water.

212
00:16:55,767 --> 00:16:57,400
They didn't believe us, Mom.

213
00:16:57,467 --> 00:16:59,667
They didn't let us in.

214
00:17:01,700 --> 00:17:05,700
Didn't you talk to the head
of security to explain?

215
00:17:05,767 --> 00:17:08,700
They brought us
to the security office.

216
00:17:08,767 --> 00:17:12,033
And we told them
why we were chasing the woman.

217
00:17:12,100 --> 00:17:15,800
But when they asked us
if we knew her name

218
00:17:15,900 --> 00:17:18,633
and if we filed a case
against her...

219
00:17:19,767 --> 00:17:21,467
we couldn't say anything.

220
00:17:23,800 --> 00:17:26,233
You can't blame the guards.

221
00:17:26,300 --> 00:17:29,200
They're just doing their job.

222
00:17:29,267 --> 00:17:32,067
And it's true,
you don't have enough proof

223
00:17:32,133 --> 00:17:35,000
against the woman
you're chasing.

224
00:17:35,067 --> 00:17:38,533
You're lucky they didn't file
a complaint against you

225
00:17:38,600 --> 00:17:41,267
for making a scene.

226
00:18:50,000 --> 00:18:52,433
Please help me, please.

227
00:18:52,500 --> 00:18:55,800
I don't want to be here anymore!

228
00:19:14,500 --> 00:19:15,700
Hi, Mookie.

229
00:19:17,533 --> 00:19:19,900
No one can hear you screaming.

230
00:19:21,233 --> 00:19:22,600
Flor is gone.

231
00:19:23,567 --> 00:19:26,233
No one can hear you scream.

232
00:19:28,267 --> 00:19:29,267
You know what?

233
00:19:30,700 --> 00:19:33,967
I'm getting tired
of chasing you,

234
00:19:34,033 --> 00:19:35,867
every time you escape.

235
00:19:38,333 --> 00:19:39,633
So now...

236
00:19:43,367 --> 00:19:47,800
I need to put you
in a medically induced coma.

237
00:19:49,300 --> 00:19:50,000
What?

238
00:19:51,367 --> 00:19:52,200
Coma?

239
00:19:53,600 --> 00:19:57,033
Now, I can assure...

240
00:19:58,033 --> 00:20:01,767
that you can never leave me.

241
00:20:01,867 --> 00:20:05,633
You will be like a living doll.

242
00:20:07,167 --> 00:20:11,333
My living doll.

243
00:20:23,000 --> 00:20:24,333
Mommy, please.

244
00:20:34,167 --> 00:20:34,967
Emma.

245
00:20:36,900 --> 00:20:39,033
You haven't changed
your clothes yet.

246
00:20:39,100 --> 00:20:40,667
You went straight
into washing the clothes.

247
00:20:42,300 --> 00:20:44,767
Dan, where will we find
that woman?

248
00:20:44,833 --> 00:20:47,933
We don't even know her name.
We don't know where she went.

249
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:49,300
We don't know
what she looks like.

250
00:20:49,367 --> 00:20:51,400
Only Bukoy saw her.

251
00:20:52,300 --> 00:20:54,433
Emma.

252
00:20:54,500 --> 00:20:58,467
- That's enough.
- Dan, we were so close to her.

253
00:20:58,533 --> 00:20:59,900
Why didn't we catch her?

254
00:20:59,967 --> 00:21:01,367
We couldn't see
what our daughter's

255
00:21:01,433 --> 00:21:03,800
kidnapper looked like.

256
00:21:07,167 --> 00:21:08,733
Emma! Emma! Emma!

257
00:21:08,833 --> 00:21:09,900
Emma! Emma!

258
00:21:09,967 --> 00:21:11,633
- Flor.
- Please help Mookie.

259
00:21:11,700 --> 00:21:13,267
Please help her. Save her.

260
00:21:13,333 --> 00:21:14,567
What happened?

261
00:21:14,633 --> 00:21:17,600
Ma'am Olive locked her up
and chained her.

262
00:21:17,667 --> 00:21:19,833
- What?
- What? Why?

263
00:21:19,900 --> 00:21:22,733
Mookie found out she's not sick.

264
00:21:22,800 --> 00:21:25,133
Ma'am Olive
just made everything up.

265
00:21:25,200 --> 00:21:28,367
And here's more,
Ma'am Olive is giving her

266
00:21:28,433 --> 00:21:30,200
veterinary medicines.

267
00:21:30,267 --> 00:21:31,033
What?

268
00:21:32,567 --> 00:21:33,733
Darn that Olive.

269
00:21:33,800 --> 00:21:36,467
Here I am, longing and
searching for my child.

270
00:21:36,533 --> 00:21:38,233
But she's hurting
her child in return.

271
00:21:38,300 --> 00:21:41,033
While she has her child
with her and loves her.

272
00:21:41,100 --> 00:21:43,400
Go to Mookie.
I'll follow you.

273
00:21:43,500 --> 00:21:44,633
I'll go to the barangay office
first.

274
00:21:44,700 --> 00:21:46,033
I'll make a report
to barangay captain.

275
00:21:46,100 --> 00:21:47,167
- Go.
- Let's go.

276
00:21:47,233 --> 00:21:48,100
- Hurry.
- Come on, come on! Let's go!

277
00:21:48,167 --> 00:21:49,267
Be careful!

278
00:21:49,333 --> 00:21:50,500
Let's hurry!

279
00:21:53,333 --> 00:21:58,033
This will turn you
to a living doll, Mookie.

280
00:21:59,367 --> 00:22:04,167
You can never move your hands,
your feet...

281
00:22:05,367 --> 00:22:07,433
and your whole body.

282
00:22:11,567 --> 00:22:12,867
Drink up.

283
00:22:20,133 --> 00:22:21,400
Drink it!

284
00:22:21,467 --> 00:22:23,067
Stop resisting, Mookie!

285
00:22:24,833 --> 00:22:26,700
Don't spit it out! Drink it!

286
00:22:28,000 --> 00:22:29,600
I said drink it!

287
00:22:34,433 --> 00:22:35,367
Mookie!

288
00:22:37,533 --> 00:22:38,733
Darn it!

289
00:22:48,500 --> 00:22:50,100
Mookie!

290
00:22:50,167 --> 00:22:51,900
- Mookie!
- Emma, Emma, Emma!

291
00:22:51,967 --> 00:22:54,900
Not that way! Over here! Hurry!

292
00:22:54,967 --> 00:22:56,533
What right do you have
to come here

293
00:22:56,600 --> 00:22:58,800
and look for
someone else's child?

294
00:22:58,867 --> 00:23:01,367
I know what you did to Mookie.

295
00:23:01,433 --> 00:23:02,867
Bring Mookie out.

296
00:23:12,333 --> 00:23:13,433
Just wait for me here.

297
00:23:13,500 --> 00:23:15,333
Why does it seem like
you don't want me to see Mookie?

298
00:23:15,400 --> 00:23:17,600
That woman is a beast.

299
00:23:17,667 --> 00:23:21,033
The village cops must get
into Olive's house.

300
00:23:21,100 --> 00:23:24,433
So they can see
what she's doing to Mookie.

301
00:23:24,533 --> 00:23:26,800
They already know
your situation.

302
00:23:26,867 --> 00:23:29,033
We need to leave.

303
00:23:29,100 --> 00:23:30,633
We need to get away.

304
00:23:30,700 --> 00:23:34,033
Mookie can stay with me if you
want to keep her away from Emma.

305
00:23:34,100 --> 00:23:35,867
I'll take care of her.

306
00:23:35,933 --> 00:23:38,367
What do you know
about caring for a child?

307
00:23:38,433 --> 00:23:39,867
You don't have a family.

308
00:23:39,933 --> 00:23:42,833
The barangay officers said
it'll be sufficient evidence

309
00:23:42,900 --> 00:23:45,833
if we catch Olive
hurting Mookie.

310
00:23:45,900 --> 00:23:47,033
It's hard to accept,

311
00:23:47,100 --> 00:23:49,800
but we have no power
against Olive.

312
00:23:49,867 --> 00:23:55,500
I don't want anyone to know
about this new rest house.

313
00:23:55,600 --> 00:23:56,867
Do you understand?

314
00:23:58,400 --> 00:24:00,100
What do we do?

315
00:24:00,167 --> 00:24:02,333
Are we just going
to abandon Mookie?
